Page 2: The Architectural Layer (N-Independent Tiles)

Divide and Conquer Pipeline – 6-step deterministic loop:
Intent Harvesting: Topological scan of 1-2 Billion RAW human queries (scaled in production).
Unsupervised Triage: Hard-wired Gate maps intent to a specific Domain_ID.
Partitioning: Global LLM dataset shredded into N domain silos.
Silicon Tiles: N independent LLMs (50M–100M parameters each) with Domain-Specific Tokenization.
Memory: 75/25 Hybrid split — 75% Sovereign ROM (immutable “Brutal Facts”), 25% Sovereign SRAM (Active Expert Vault).
Execution: Activation in <5 ns, with immediate 0V power-down upon completion.
Tile Discovery & Evolution – 3-Year Unsupervised Cycle
Every 3 years, the system performs a massive unsupervised learning pass on 2–3 trillion aggregated, anonymized user queries.
Deterministic topological clustering identifies natural intent clusters.
The system automatically generates or refines precise Tile Names and determines the optimal number of Tiles N.
The global knowledge base is re-shredded according to the new boundaries.
Universal axioms and common knowledge constants are duplicated across all Tiles (Redundancy Rule).
Domain-Specific Token Dictionaries (500–1000 tokens per Tile) are rebuilt.
The resulting Tile definitions, names, and partitioning rules are frozen into Sovereign ROM for the next 3-year period. This ensures long-term stability and determinism while allowing controlled, data-driven evolution under National Authority oversight.




